<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="19" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1436,410,1146]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,281,410,436]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Males are easily recognised from other 
<taxonomicName box="[759,997,410,436]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Erigonoplus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[759,904,410,435]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Erigonoplus</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
by the bladder like cephalic tubercle (
<figureCitation box="[159,246,448,474]" captionStart="FIGURES 30–42" captionStartId="19.[151,271,1868,1892]" captionText="FIGURES 30–42. Figs 30–36. Erigonoplus castellanus (O.P.-Cambridge, 1875); 30. Male prosoma, lateral view; 31. Male femur I, ventral view; 32. Male palp, prolateral view; 33. Male palpal tibia, dorsal view; 34. Embolic division, anteroventral view; 35. Epigynum, ventral view; 36. Vulva, ventral view. Figs 37–42. Erigonoplus depressifrons Simon, 1884; 37. Male prosoma, lateral view; 38. Male palp, prolateral view; 39. Male palpal tibia, dorsal view; 40. Embolic division, anteroventral view; 41. Epigynum, ventral view; 42. Vulva." pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Fig. 30</figureCitation>
), females by the abruptly narrowing median septum in the epigynum (
<figureCitation box="[1070,1158,448,474]" captionStart="FIGURES 30–42" captionStartId="19.[151,271,1868,1892]" captionText="FIGURES 30–42. Figs 30–36. Erigonoplus castellanus (O.P.-Cambridge, 1875); 30. Male prosoma, lateral view; 31. Male femur I, ventral view; 32. Male palp, prolateral view; 33. Male palpal tibia, dorsal view; 34. Embolic division, anteroventral view; 35. Epigynum, ventral view; 36. Vulva, ventral view. Figs 37–42. Erigonoplus depressifrons Simon, 1884; 37. Male prosoma, lateral view; 38. Male palp, prolateral view; 39. Male palpal tibia, dorsal view; 40. Embolic division, anteroventral view; 41. Epigynum, ventral view; 42. Vulva." pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Fig. 35</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="19" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1436,410,1146]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,353,485,511]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Description:</emphasis>
Male: Measurements: Total length 1.8; prosoma 0.61–0.70 long, 0.54–0.56 wide. Colour: Prosoma yellow-brown, suffused with blackish brown at thoracic part, legs dull orange, abdomen black. Prosoma (
<figureCitation box="[270,360,560,586]" captionStart="FIGURES 30–42" captionStartId="19.[151,271,1868,1892]" captionText="FIGURES 30–42. Figs 30–36. Erigonoplus castellanus (O.P.-Cambridge, 1875); 30. Male prosoma, lateral view; 31. Male femur I, ventral view; 32. Male palp, prolateral view; 33. Male palpal tibia, dorsal view; 34. Embolic division, anteroventral view; 35. Epigynum, ventral view; 36. Vulva, ventral view. Figs 37–42. Erigonoplus depressifrons Simon, 1884; 37. Male prosoma, lateral view; 38. Male palp, prolateral view; 39. Male palpal tibia, dorsal view; 40. Embolic division, anteroventral view; 41. Epigynum, ventral view; 42. Vulva." pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Fig. 30</figureCitation>
): With very peculiar, bladder like tubercle, not carrying any eyes and constricted above the eye region. Legs: Femur I ventrally with 12 spines (
<figureCitation box="[767,855,597,623]" captionStart="FIGURES 30–42" captionStartId="19.[151,271,1868,1892]" captionText="FIGURES 30–42. Figs 30–36. Erigonoplus castellanus (O.P.-Cambridge, 1875); 30. Male prosoma, lateral view; 31. Male femur I, ventral view; 32. Male palp, prolateral view; 33. Male palpal tibia, dorsal view; 34. Embolic division, anteroventral view; 35. Epigynum, ventral view; 36. Vulva, ventral view. Figs 37–42. Erigonoplus depressifrons Simon, 1884; 37. Male prosoma, lateral view; 38. Male palp, prolateral view; 39. Male palpal tibia, dorsal view; 40. Embolic division, anteroventral view; 41. Epigynum, ventral view; 42. Vulva." pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Fig. 31</figureCitation>
); Ti I–II with spines broken off, Ti III–IV with 1 dorsal spine; Tb Mt II = 0.40. Palp (
<figureCitation box="[582,722,634,660]" captionStart="FIGURES 30–42" captionStartId="19.[151,271,1868,1892]" captionText="FIGURES 30–42. Figs 30–36. Erigonoplus castellanus (O.P.-Cambridge, 1875); 30. Male prosoma, lateral view; 31. Male femur I, ventral view; 32. Male palp, prolateral view; 33. Male palpal tibia, dorsal view; 34. Embolic division, anteroventral view; 35. Epigynum, ventral view; 36. Vulva, ventral view. Figs 37–42. Erigonoplus depressifrons Simon, 1884; 37. Male prosoma, lateral view; 38. Male palp, prolateral view; 39. Male palpal tibia, dorsal view; 40. Embolic division, anteroventral view; 41. Epigynum, ventral view; 42. Vulva." pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Figs 32–34</figureCitation>
): Tibia bent in the middle, distally with triangular prolateral and retrolateral apophyses; paracymbium J-shaped; radix and tail-piece wide, forming an angle of 90°; embolus compact, distally with small triangular tooth.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1436,410,1146]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,299,746,772]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Female:</emphasis>
Total length 1.8–1.9; prosoma 0.73 long, 0.57 wide. Legs: Spine formula 2211; L Sp Ti I = 0.8, P Sp Ti I = 0.21; Tb I = 0.38. Epigynum (
<figureCitation box="[656,752,784,810]" captionStart="FIGURES 30–42" captionStartId="19.[151,271,1868,1892]" captionText="FIGURES 30–42. Figs 30–36. Erigonoplus castellanus (O.P.-Cambridge, 1875); 30. Male prosoma, lateral view; 31. Male femur I, ventral view; 32. Male palp, prolateral view; 33. Male palpal tibia, dorsal view; 34. Embolic division, anteroventral view; 35. Epigynum, ventral view; 36. Vulva, ventral view. Figs 37–42. Erigonoplus depressifrons Simon, 1884; 37. Male prosoma, lateral view; 38. Male palp, prolateral view; 39. Male palpal tibia, dorsal view; 40. Embolic division, anteroventral view; 41. Epigynum, ventral view; 42. Vulva." pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Fig. 35</figureCitation>
): With trapezoid atrium, divided by a median septum, narrowing towards the base. Vulva (
<figureCitation box="[574,663,821,847]" captionStart="FIGURES 30–42" captionStartId="19.[151,271,1868,1892]" captionText="FIGURES 30–42. Figs 30–36. Erigonoplus castellanus (O.P.-Cambridge, 1875); 30. Male prosoma, lateral view; 31. Male femur I, ventral view; 32. Male palp, prolateral view; 33. Male palpal tibia, dorsal view; 34. Embolic division, anteroventral view; 35. Epigynum, ventral view; 36. Vulva, ventral view. Figs 37–42. Erigonoplus depressifrons Simon, 1884; 37. Male prosoma, lateral view; 38. Male palp, prolateral view; 39. Male palpal tibia, dorsal view; 40. Embolic division, anteroventral view; 41. Epigynum, ventral view; 42. Vulva." pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Fig. 36</figureCitation>
): Spermathecae suboval, separated by their maximal diameter.
</paragraph>
